  "elapsed_s": 205.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But there also were living in Dobra other nationalities-- Russians, Germans predominantly, they were probably the second largest minority, and some Belorussians [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and Lithuanians.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that was a sort of a mix of four or five different nationalities and-- and races.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, commercial city, it was-- a commercial city it was not.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Dobra was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] rather unimportant agricultural city.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't believe that Dobra has supplied internationally its products.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it has fed the local population.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Farmers from nearby-- pardon me-- brought their wares to the city, brought their goods to the city-- to the little town, rather.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And where trade was principally between the townspeople and the people that came with eggs and chickens and cows and ducks and-- and things to sell and wheat and-- and corn and things like that, they usually bought from the city coal and seeds and clothing and shoes and whatever the small-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] people having small businesses in the city were producing.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The street was [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The number, it only seems to me remotely as being somewhat near 196 or 98.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was at the outskirts of the city.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And generally, our neighbors were generally non-Jews, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] with which we lived in a sense, up till a certain point, in a good committee and a good understanding and a neighborhood kind of an atmosphere, with tolerating one another and living with one another.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Those are the memories of mine when I was a young man, up till about the age of 13 or 14, when I was [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] exposed to the first anti-Jewish [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] first anti-Jewish feeling that was expressed to me by friends and by neighbors.",
      "word_count": 50
    }
  ],
